{
  "name": "rad-website-design",
  "version": "0.3.0",
  "description": "Static-analysis design review and concrete fix proposals for existing HTML/CSS/JSX/Astro source. Four pure-stdlib Python validators (viewport-meta presence + `user-scalable=no` detection, pure black/white eye-strain scan, sub-44px tap-target detection, CLS-risk pattern scan for `<img>` / `<iframe>` / `<video>` without dimensions and `@font-face` without `font-display: swap`) run before LLM judgment. One autonomous reviewer agent. Knowledge skills cover must-do baseline, should-do recommendations, severity-tiered anti-patterns with damage cited from research, Calm UX aesthetic direction, agentic UX patterns, and AEO/llms.txt with adoption caveats. Honest scope: does NOT run Lighthouse, does NOT run axe-core at runtime, does NOT measure Core Web Vitals (only catches source-level causes), does NOT take screenshots, does NOT render JS-heavy SPAs. Findings tagged [STATIC] / [HEURISTIC] / [NEEDS-MANUAL]; no Pass/Fail verdict. For new design generation, pair with `frontend-design`. For runtime/visual verification, pair with chrome-devtools-mcp + Lighthouse. For deeper accessibility, pair with rad-a11y.",
